From: engels@darkstar ()
Subject: Re: fig2dev port anywhere?
Date: 1 Dec 1993 16:59:15 GMT
Reply-To: engelsg@uni-duesseldorf.de

T.J. (mtja@dcs.ed.ac.uk) wrote:
: Sorry if this is a FAQ, but is there a Linux port of fig2dev anywhere?
: I've tried all the Linux archives and can't find it anywhere. I've also
: tried compiling from the source myself...that failed miserably. I want to
: be able to place Fig files in my LaTeX documents, but when I try to
: export the file as an eps file, XFig complains that it can't find fig2dev.

I'm using Xfig with fig2dev and found it as a part of the
transfig package, but I have allready forgotten were I found it (I think 
on a sunsite mirror). If you can't find it, mail me.   

Btw: we use PiCTeX as export format, so we can see the pictures in the
previewer.

engelsg@uni-duesseldorf.de





------------------------------

From: engels@darkstar ()
Subject: Re: TeX, SGML, and graphics?
Date: 1 Dec 1993 17:13:42 GMT
Reply-To: engelsg@uni-duesseldorf.de

Phil Perucci (philp@universe.digex.net) wrote:
: I currently use LaTeX, but would like to be able to generate 
: circles, boxes, lines, etc. for flow-charts.  Is there
: anything available (language) that can do "graphics".  I have
: used idraw, but am looking for a language - not interactive.

We use Xfig (interactive) to produce PiCTeX output. We also use 
PiCTeX command to generate graphics via programs that we wrote at 
our insitute. In other words: PiCTeX is a language which describes
pictures, but it is not restricted like LaTeX concerning line slopes 
or size of circles.

Btw: PiCTeX is free, as far as I know the manual is not. We use
a (german) book from Helmut Kopka, which describes PiCTeX. The 
german title is ''LaTeX Erweiterungsmoeglichkeiten'' (LaTeX 
extensions). I don't know if there you can find an english version of 
this book.

I know that there is a special style or program to produce flow 
charts, but I don't know the name. Maybe you should ask again in 
comp.text.tex. Look out for a list of style files. 

engelsg@uni-duesseldorf.de



