Acording to a unix wizard you can create a directory /tarz which sees opens,
etc and mangles things so /tarz/foo/bar is /foo/bar but with .tar and .tar.Z
files converted into dirs. So if /foo/bar/baz.tar.Z exists you can do
cd /tarz/foo/bar/baz as if it was a normal dir with automatic untaring and
uncompression (read only access for everybody inc. superuser is planned).

