>c> our new Linux CD-ROM distribution, a $39 value, along with a
>c> coupon for $10 off any purchase.

>sure is a cheap and easy way to build an address database
>of Linux users...

True.. But years ago, when my dad worked for NCR.. I grabbed one of those
free subscription forms from an Infoworld.. and like sent it in saying I was
a director of purchasing for some gizallion dollar company.. so I wouldn't
have to wait a week to read the X.Cringe collumn :).. and now, several years
later, I get such an amazing array of junk in the mail, you wouldn't believe!
Every fly-by-night company in the free world sends me flyers about their
wasteoid database program (with complimentry WinDoze cartoon calendar)! Those
folks with the free CD can send me anything they want.. chances are it'll get
lost under one of Microsoft's triplicate mailings and I'll never see it!

Moral of the story: If you'r going to fill out free subscription forms,
make sure they come from either Beverage World or that the new Linux Journel.
That and direct mailings stink, unless its one of those cool minute-man flyers
trying to see you a giga-watt UPS. :)
 
What group is this again?
 
Christopher
cjs@netcom.com

    

