Subject: Re: Too Many Messages
From: john.will@satalink.com (John Will)
Date: Mon, 29 Nov 93 20:45:00 -0640

D >All this cross-posting is a main reason why the volume is so high!  The
D >point of the breakup of c.o.l was to be more specific in the intended 
D >audience. If everything is cross-posted, it defeats the purpose.

The PRECISE reason that I continue to vote against splitting newsgroups
into multiples, far too few folks post into the correct ones, and many
just post into all of them, kinda' defeats the purpose of splitting them!
If you had one huge newsgroup, it would be self-limiting to an extent, when
it got 100's of messages a day, the less determined would drop out. :-)

