Date: Wed, 1 Dec 1993 22:08:19 GMT

In <CHDHrC.JwI@cs.vu.nl> rmast@cs.vu.nl (Mast RN) writes:
>zxmgv07@studserv.zdv.uni-tuebingen.de (Michael Will) writes:

>>please stop writing about TeX versa WYSIWYG, it will only result in people
>>being humilitated since it is a religious question :-)

>I want to start a new religion! What about a WYSIWYG TeX editor?

Yeah!  Me too.  I know that TeX has to read a file multiple times, but
that seems like a simple problem to work around.  If someone else
followed the original flame-fest to the end, could they summarize the
results for the rest of us that gave up?

I use _both_ TeX and FrameMaker, and I can see valid uses for both of
them.  I see advantages and disadvantages in each that aren't in the other,
(and vice versa).  IMHO, an editor that combines both would be way cool.

I know that this has been beaten to death already, I just wanted to know
what the obituary reads. :-)

